			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No.<br /><br />When $2002 is read, a &quot; latch&quot;  is reset. The latch point to the number 1 or 0. Eevry time you write to $2006 or $2006, the latch toggles. So to write it, you need to set the latch to a known position. Reading it sets it to 0, or cleared. Then the next write to $2006/$2005 will go to the first position. The next will go to the 2nd position. then the 1st, 2nd, etc.<br /><br />Read the Wiki page on PPU registers for a better understanding.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
