			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You write only two bytes to $2005, but the bits in those bytes are sort of &quot;scattered&quot; in a way that makes sense for scrolling.<br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>The first write to $2005 writes to coarse and fine X at the same time. Bits 2-0 go to the fine X register that controls the delay line mux used for scrolling 0-7 pixels, while bits 7-3 go to the coarse X portion of a register called &quot;t&quot; by the &quot;skinny&quot; doc. </li><li>The second write to $2005 writes to coarse and fine Y at the same time. The written bits go to two different parts of &quot;t&quot;. </li></ol>After you finish uploading data to VRAM through $2006 and $2007, &quot;t&quot; is corrupted. You need to fix &quot;t&quot; by writing to $2000 once and $2005 twice just before turning on rendering.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

